 The set is convex.
 Let 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
S=\left\{ x\in\mathbb{R}^{n}\big|x+S_{2}\subset S_{1}\right\} 
\]

\end_inset

and 
\begin_inset Formula $x_{1},x_{2}\in S$
\end_inset

.
 Fix an arbitrary 
\begin_inset Formula $s_{2}\in S_{2}$
\end_inset

.
 Since 
\begin_inset Formula $x_{1}\in S$
\end_inset

 it's the case that 
\begin_inset Formula $x_{1}+s_{2}\in S_{1}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $x_{2}+s_{2}\in S_{1}$
\end_inset

.
 Now consider 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda x_{1}+\left(1-\lambda\right)x_{2}$
\end_inset

.
 Since 
\begin_inset Formula $S_{1}$
\end_inset

 is convex 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda\left(x_{1}+s_{2}\right)+\left(1-\lambda\right)\left(x_{2}+s_{2}\right)\in S_{1}$
\end_inset

 but 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
\lambda\left(x_{1}+s_{2}\right)+\left(1-\lambda\right)\left(x_{2}+s_{2}\right) & =\left(\lambda x_{1}+\left(1-\lambda\right)x_{2}\right)+\lambda s_{2}+\left(1-\lambda\right)s_{2}\\
 & =\left(\lambda x_{1}+\left(1-\lambda\right)x_{2}\right)+s_{2}
\end{align*}

\end_inset

and therefore 
\begin_inset Formula $S$
\end_inset

