The set is convex.
 Let 
\begin_inset Formula $S\subset\mathbb{R}^{n}$
\end_inset

 be the set 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\left\{ x\in\mathbb{R}^{n}\big|x^{\intercal}Ax+b^{\intercal}x+c\leq0,g^{\intercal}x+h=0\right\} 
\]

\end_inset

Since 
\begin_inset Formula $A+\lambda gg^{\intercal}$
\end_inset

 is PSD it's the case that 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
S'=\left\{ x\in\mathbb{R}^{n}\big|x^{\intercal}\left(A+\lambda gg^{\intercal}\right)x+b^{\intercal}x+c\leq0\right\} 
\]

\end_inset

is convex.
 Why? Diagonalize and complete the square to get the constraint into the
 form 
\begin_inset Formula $x^{\intercal}Bx\leq k$
\end_inset

 (note that 
\begin_inset Formula $B\succeq0$
\end_inset

) and some 
\begin_inset Formula $k$
\end_inset

.
 If 
\begin_inset Formula $k\geq0$
\end_inset

 then the set is convex.
 If 
\begin_inset Formula $k<0$
\end_inset

 then the set is empty and trivially convex.
 Then manipulating the constraint characterizing 
\begin_inset Formula $S'$
\end_inset

 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
x^{\intercal}\left(A+\lambda gg^{\intercal}\right)x+b^{\intercal}x+c & =x^{\intercal}Ax+x^{\intercal}\lambda gg^{\intercal}x+b^{\intercal}x+c\\
 & =x^{\intercal}Ax+\lambda\left\Vert g^{\intercal}x\right\Vert ^{2}+b^{\intercal}+c\\
 & =x^{\intercal}Ax+b^{\intercal}+c+\lambda h^{2}
\end{align*}

\end_inset

and therefore 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
x^{\intercal}\left(A+\lambda gg^{\intercal}\right)x+b^{\intercal}+c-\lambda h^{2}=x^{\intercal}Ax+b^{\intercal}+c
\]

\end_inset

but again since 
\begin_inset Formula $A+\lambda gg^{\intercal}$
\end_inset

 is PSD 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\left\{ x\in\mathbb{R}^{n}\big|x^{\intercal}\left(A+\lambda gg^{\intercal}\right)x+b^{\intercal}+c-\lambda h^{2}\leq-\lambda h^{2}\right\} 
\]

\end_inset

is also convex (by the same argument as before except with 
\begin_inset Formula $k'=k-\lambda h^{2}$
\end_inset

).
 Hence 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\left\{ x\in\mathbb{R}^{n}\big|x^{\intercal}Ax+b^{\intercal}+c\leq-\lambda h^{2}\right\} 
\]

\end_inset

is convex and since the intersection of two convex sets (the plane 
\begin_inset Formula $g^{\intercal}x+h=0$
\end_inset

 is convex) is convex the set 
\begin_inset Formula $S$
\end_inset

 is convex.
\end_layout

