\begin_inset Formula $\sum\alpha_{i}$
\end_inset

 we get that 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
y^{'}\coloneqq\frac{1}{\sum_{i}\alpha}y=\sum_{i=1}^{m}\alpha_{i}^{'}x_{i}
\]

\end_inset

is a convex combination of the 
\begin_inset Formula $x_{i}$
\end_inset

 and therefore 
\begin_inset Formula $y^{'}\in C$
\end_inset

 (since 
\begin_inset Formula $C$
\end_inset

