\end_inset

 for all 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha\in\left[0,1\right]$
\end_inset

.
 Finally 
\begin_inset Formula $R\left(x\right)$
\end_inset

 is closed because 
\begin_inset Formula $C$
\end_inset

 is closed: let 
\begin_inset Formula $z_{k}\rightarrow z$
\end_inset

 be a convergent sequence in 
\begin_inset Formula $R\left(x\right)$
\end_inset

.
 Fix a 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda$
\end_inset

 and then for each 
\begin_inset Formula $k$
\end_inset

 we have that 
\begin_inset Formula $x_{k}=x+\lambda z_{k}\in C$
\end_inset

.
 Then since 
\begin_inset Formula $C$
\end_inset

 is closed 
\begin_inset Formula $\lim_{k\rightarrow\infty}x_{k}\in C$
\end_inset

 and hence 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\lim_{k\rightarrow\infty}x_{k}=\lim_{k\rightarrow\infty}\left(x+\lambda z_{k}\right)=x+\lambda\lim_{k\rightarrow\infty}z_{k}=x+\lambda z\in C
\]

\end_inset


